INTERNSCTL(1)

NAME
       internsctl - A CLI tool to manage system information and users

SYNOPSIS
       internsctl [OPTIONS] COMMAND

DESCRIPTION
       internsctl is a command-line tool that provides various functionalities
       related to system information, user management, and file details.

OPTIONS
       -v, --version
              Show the version of internsctl.

       -h, --help
              Display this help message.

COMMANDS
       cpu getinfo
              Get CPU information using the lscpu command.

       memory getinfo
              Get memory information using the free command.

       user create <username>
              Create a new user with a corresponding home directory.

       user list [--sudo-only]
              List all regular users on the Linux server [with sudo permissions].

       file getinfo [OPTIONS] <filename>
              Get information about a specific file.

FILE GETINFO OPTIONS
       -s, --size
              Print only the file size.

       -p, --permissions
              Print only file permissions.

       -o, --owner
              Print only the file owner.

       -m, --last-modified
              Print last modified date.

EXAMPLES
       To get CPU information:
              $ internsctl cpu getinfo

       To create a new user:
              $ internsctl user create myuser

       To list all users with sudo permissions:
              $ internsctl user list --sudo-only

       To get information about a file:
              $ internsctl file getinfo -s example.txt

